name: SUB FUNC | 02 - 02 | UPDATE | Supplier Site Details - Address + OU Validate
description:
This recipe automates the process of updating supplier address and operational unit data in a database based on provided vendor information.

- The process begins by executing a recipe function that accepts parameters related to a vendor, including a vendor ID and other relevant details.
- It first truncates existing records in the Supplier Address and Supplier Operational Unit data tables to prepare for new data.
- The recipe then retrieves records from a temporary data table based on the provided vendor ID and processes each record to extract relevant address details.
- For each record, it checks for specific address-related information and updates or inserts records into the Supplier Address DataTable with the parsed address data.
- It also checks for various flags and details related to tax applicability and purchasing status, updating corresponding variables as necessary.
- The recipe continues to search for and update additional fields such as bank instructions, tax registration status, and payment methods based on the retrieved records.
- Finally, it performs a final upsert operation to ensure all relevant data is accurately reflected in the Supplier Operational Unit DataTable.

In case of any errors during execution, the recipe logs the error and calls an error handling recipe to notify the relevant stakeholders via email, including details about the failure and any attached files if applicable.
